narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class to other students, it's fun and Maya is the best
This class is a challenging intermediate course that requires a lot of weekly work, but is graded very fairly and the exams are very much in line with what we cover in class.

Definitely especially if you have just come through the L1 L2 track (because you have no choice) but more importantly because you have just spent 12 months learning the basics of Latin for the purpose of translating real prose/poetry. I preferred this course because I enjoy Latin prose more than Lain poetry. That may be a consideration for someone debating which mid-level Latin course to take.
